        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:56PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 555 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 9 miles north of
Turtle Lake, or 24 miles east of Garrison, moving southeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Turtle Lake, Mercer, and Strawberry Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
